---
// import { Image } from 'astro:assets'
// import profileImage from '../../public/images/placeholder.webp'
---

<div class="flex flex-col md:gap-5 gap-3 overflow-y-auto no-scrollbar max-h-130 md:max-h-140">
    <!-- profile image and introduction -->
     <div class="w-full flex justify-between gap-3">
        <!-- the image holder -->
        <div class="aspect-square w-[20%] overflow-hidden rounded-md border-1 hidden md:block">
            <img src="/images/newHeadshotCrop.webp" alt="headshot" class="h-full object-cover">
        </div>

        <!-- the intro paragraph -->
        <div class="md:w-[70%] border-1 rounded-md w-full text-xs p-3 flex flex-col gap-2">
            <p class="font-semibold">About Me</p>
            <p>I went from producing music to producing web applications. My professional background as a music producer taught me how to ship creative projects on deadline and now I apply that same discipline to building software.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="w-full flex flex-col text-xs border-1 rounded-md p-3 gap-2">
        <!-- <p class="font-semibold">Why I Code</p> -->
        <p>Transitioning from music to programming taught me the most valuable skill: rapid learning and adaptation. Whether I'm implementing Firebase authentication for the first time or integrating unfamiliar APIs, I thrive on figuring things out.</p>
        <p>I've built 8+ live web applications, each one teaching me something new about various technologies, architectures, and experiences.</p>
    </div>


    <p class="text-xs w-full text-center font-semibold">Tech Stack</p>
    <hr class="opacity-50">

    <!-- the tech scroll -->
    <div class="relative w-full">
        <div class="flex overflow-x-auto gap-4 relative no-scrollbar text-almost-white opacity-100 text-xs text-nowrap">
            <!-- copy techs below -->
            <div class="px-4 py-2 text-center react-gradient rounded-lg shadow-sm transition-all cursor-default">
                React
            </div>
            <div class="px-4 py-2 text-center astro-gradient rounded-lg shadow-sm transition-all cursor-default">
                Astro
            </div>
            <div class="px-4 py-2 text-center tailwind-gradient rounded-lg shadow-sm transition-all cursor-default">
                Tailwind
            </div>
            <div class="px-4 py-2 text-center git-gradient rounded-lg shadow-sm transition-all cursor-default">
                Git
            </div>
            <div class="px-4 py-2 text-center vite-gradient rounded-lg shadow-sm transition-all cursor-default">
                Vite
            </div>
            <div class="px-4 py-2 text-center unity-gradient rounded-lg shadow-sm transition-all cursor-default">
                Unity/C#
            </div>
            <div class="px-4 py-2 text-center godot-gradient rounded-lg shadow-sm transition-all cursor-default">
                GDScript
            </div>
            <div class="px-4 py-2 text-center js-gradient rounded-lg shadow-sm transition-all cursor-default">
                JavaScript
            </div>
            <div class="px-4 py-2 text-center js-gradient rounded-lg shadow-sm transition-all cursor-default">
                TypeScript
            </div>
            <div class="px-4 py-2 text-center css-gradient rounded-lg shadow-sm transition-all cursor-default">
                CSS
            </div>
            <div class="px-4 py-2 text-center cf-gradient rounded-lg shadow-sm transition-all cursor-default">
                CloudFlare Pages
            </div>
        </div>
        <!-- fades -->
        <div class="pointer-events-none absolute top-0 bottom-0 left-0 w-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-almost-white dark:from-almost-black to-transparent"></div>
        <div class="pointer-events-none absolute top-0 bottom-0 right-0 w-8 bg-gradient-to-l from-almost-white dark:from-almost-black to-transparent"></div>
    </div>


    <div class="w-full flex flex-col text-xs rounded-md py-2 px-3 gap-2 border-1">
        <p class="font-semibold">Reach Out!</p>
        <p>Actively seeking junior developer or entry-level programming roles where I can contribute to real-world projects and continue growing as a developer.</p>
        <p>Reach out anytime! Looking forward to hearing from you!</p>
    </div>

</div>